Five persons were injured on Friday evening when another bomb exploded in Jalingo, the Taraba State capital. An eyewitness, Danlami Kwambo, told The Nation the explosion occurred around 7:30 pm at the palace of the Ward Head in Nukkai area of Jalingo. He said some unsuspecting persons dropped a black polythene bag, asking people to watch over it after which they left.   2023: Tinubu, Sanwoolu have done enough to win for APC…     2023: The trouble within Oyo PDP     Delta 2023: Omo-Agege’s mother of all declarations   It was suspected that the bag contained the explosives. He said youths in the area went on rampage over the incident before the intervention of some elders in the area calmed the situation. Taraba experienced an explosion a few days ago in Iware,  Ardo Kola LGA which killed six persons and left several injured..